                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)/3366a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-20T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 20, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. Your 345, September 18, 1 p.m. has been repeated to London.<note n="31"
                        xml:id="d1017fn31">In telegram No. 3935, <hi rend="italic"
                        >infra</hi>.</note> The Department has added that it is inclined to concur
                    with your suggestion but has instructed the Embassy to discuss the matter with
                    the British authorities and afford them an opportunity for comment <pb
                        facs="0954" n="946" xml:id="pg_946"/> before action is taken here. A reply
                    by Tuesday<note n="32" xml:id="d1017fn32">September 23.</note> at the latest has
                    been requested.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile, please inform the Turkish authorities that your Government attaches
                    the greatest importance to chrome and has the matter under urgent consideration.
                    You should if you find it necessary insist that the Turkish Government avoid any
                    agreement with Germany regarding chrome until we have had an opportunity to
                    present our views to the Turkish authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
